keyFacts: Jeffrey E. Epstein, as president of Laurel Inc., transferred property to a church religious organization called Bliss Inc. for only $200.
The transaction occurred on March 9, 2019, but was not recorded until October 23, 2020.
The document is a formal Warranty Deed, implying a permanent transfer of property with title warranties.
The property is located in Palm Beach County, Florida, specifically referenced as parcels in 'El Bravo Park'.
The document shows Epstein's involvement in corporate real estate transactions through Laurel Inc. well into 2019.
